<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    changes to root servers
From:       <a href="?a=95837784200005&r=1&w=2">Paul Mockapetris &lt;pvm () venera ! isi ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198711">1987-11-22 15:14:28</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927047&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927047&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

C.ISI.EDU leaves the air today.  It was removed from the list of root
servers last week.

The remaining TOPS-20 root servers (A.ISI.EDU, SRI-NIC.ARPA, and
GUNTER-ADAM.ARPA) have been upgraded to include SOA RRs in the authority
section of authoritative responses for negative caching.  This change
had the unfortunate side effect of crashing reboots of the multinet VMS
version of BIND when one of the SOA dispensing servers is first to
respond.  A fix for the VMS BIND is under development.

paul

